WEBVTT

00:01.419 --> 00:03.921
<i>♪♪ [ Newsreel Theme: March]</i>

00:05.464 --> 00:08.634
<i>[ Newsreel Narrator] The Queen Mary, the
greatest passenger liner in the world...</i>

00:08.718 --> 00:12.680
<i>brings home the greatest human cargo
New York Harbor has ever seen.</i>

00:12.763 --> 00:17.810
<i>Almost 15,000 troops
get an eager glimpse of the U.S. of A.</i>

00:17.935 --> 00:22.315
<i>Past the towers of Manhattan steams the
83,000-ton British liner.</i> [Ship Horn Blowing]

00:22.398 --> 00:24.859
<i>These victorious G.I.s
have done their duty.</i>

00:24.942 --> 00:27.028
<i>They answered their country's call,</i>

00:27.111 --> 00:30.031
<i>left their jobs, their families,
their sweethearts...</i>

00:30.114 --> 00:33.534
<i>and beat the Nazi tyranny
on a thousand battlefields.</i>

00:33.618 --> 00:38.915
<i>For some- the psychological victims of war-
it will be a long road back.</i>

00:38.998 --> 00:43.669
<i>These men will need time to rebuild the
lives they set aside when Uncle Sam called.</i>

00:43.794 --> 00:47.215
[Crowd Cheering] <i>For others- the
G.I.s of the "Dear John" letters-</i>

00:47.298 --> 00:50.551
<i>it means starting over,
replacing what they have lost.</i>

00:50.635 --> 00:55.181
<i>They faced one challenge and won.
They can win this one too.</i>

00:55.264 --> 00:57.183
<i>Welcome home.</i>

00:57.266 --> 00:59.310
<i>Let dancing replace marching.</i>

01:03.272 --> 01:05.441
<i>♪♪ [ Ends ]</i>

01:10.238 --> 01:12.240
<i>[ Woman's Voice]
I don't know how to tell you this.</i>

01:12.323 --> 01:14.242
<i>I really don't want to hurt you,</i>

01:14.325 --> 01:17.411
<i>but I just can't wait for you any longer.</i>

01:18.704 --> 01:20.915
<i>I know I promised to wait.</i>

01:20.998 --> 01:23.626
<i>I really did try,</i>

01:23.709 --> 01:27.546
<i>but it's been so much longer
than either of us expected.</i>

01:27.630 --> 01:31.384
<i>So much has happened,
and you're so far away.</i>

01:32.927 --> 01:36.305
<i>I hope you understand how I feel.</i>

01:36.389 --> 01:38.933
<i>I know I said I loved you,
but I'm young...</i>

01:39.016 --> 01:42.603
<i>and I have to live my life</i> now.

01:42.687 --> 01:45.731
<i>And who knows how long
it will be before you return.</i>

01:47.275 --> 01:50.486
<i>I hope you don't hate me
for leaving you this way.</i>

01:50.569 --> 01:54.282
<i>But perhaps, when the war is over,
we can be friends again.</i>

01:55.866 --> 01:58.244
<i>Please take care of yourself.</i>

01:58.327 --> 02:00.997
<i>I continue to worry about you.</i>

02:01.080 --> 02:03.499
<i>Sincerely, Rosemary.</i>

02:06.544 --> 02:09.547
<i>♪♪ [ Big Band Up-tempo ]</i>

02:24.437 --> 02:26.939
<i>♪♪ [ Continues ]</i>

02:31.277 --> 02:34.280
<i>[ People Chattering, Laughing,
Muffled]</i>

02:42.913 --> 02:44.999
There's Tom Caldwell's Cadillac.

02:45.082 --> 02:47.126
Well, I'll be dogged.

02:47.209 --> 02:49.253
Say, who's he going
outwith now anyway?

02:49.337 --> 02:51.339
Linda Booth.
Do you believe it?

02:51.422 --> 02:53.299
With Linda Booth?
[Chuckling]

02:53.424 --> 02:55.725
I thought she was going
out with Georgie Wise.

02:55.750 --> 02:56.826
Didn't you hear?

02:56.886 --> 02:59.847
Well, I heard Georgie joined
the air corps, all right, but-

02:59.930 --> 03:03.184
Wait a minute.
Georgie didn't get-

03:03.267 --> 03:06.228
They broke up.
[Laughing]

03:06.312 --> 03:09.190
<i>[ Horn Honks]
[ Man Shouts]</i>

03:09.273 --> 03:11.817
Will you look at that?

03:11.901 --> 03:14.820
Aw, that's just a big old boat.

03:14.904 --> 03:19.033
Sweetheart, that car
doesn't do you justice.

03:19.116 --> 03:21.452
You are precious.

03:25.206 --> 03:28.042
<i>♪♪ [ Band Continues]</i>

03:42.640 --> 03:45.601
♪♪ [Song Ends]
Now let's have a big hand for the band.

03:45.684 --> 03:48.396
Swell job, fellas.

03:48.479 --> 03:51.690
We were all saddened by the great
Glenn Miller's tragic death...

03:51.774 --> 03:54.610
somewhere in the skies
over France.

03:54.693 --> 03:57.488
But he left us a wonderful legacy
in his music.

03:57.571 --> 04:00.741
And now for all those
fine young men here tonight...

04:00.825 --> 04:02.743
just back from overseas,

04:02.827 --> 04:05.996
I'd like to ask the band to play
one of his best tunes.

04:06.122 --> 04:09.417
Oh, look. There's Pat Kingsley.
<i>[ Bandleader Continues, Indistinct ]</i>

04:09.542 --> 04:12.201
Well, Pat Kingsley just- just
came home from the Pacific.

04:12.226 --> 04:13.111
So?

04:14.130 --> 04:16.048
Come on.
Let's go up to the point.

04:16.132 --> 04:18.091
Oh, not now.
It's too early.

04:18.175 --> 04:20.511
Come on. This place is dead.
We'll come back later.

04:20.594 --> 04:24.306
<i>[ Bandleader] Folks, I bet you never
saw a more sober group of guys.</i>

04:24.390 --> 04:26.392
Hey! Keep your mitts
off my girl!

04:26.475 --> 04:30.146
The drummer told me his wife
wouldn't let him in the house...

04:30.229 --> 04:32.231
if he ever showed up again...

04:32.356 --> 04:35.901
with that little brown jug.
♪♪<i>[Rim Shots ]</i>

04:35.985 --> 04:39.697
So let's cheer him up,
and everybody swing!

04:39.780 --> 04:41.699
♪♪ [ “Little Brown Jug” ]
Who is that creep?

04:41.782 --> 04:44.952
Oh, that's just Jimmy Turner.
He takes care of this place.

04:45.035 --> 04:46.954
What does he do,
sweep it with his eye?

04:47.037 --> 04:50.249
No, but I hear he sleeps on an
old mattress in the basement.

04:50.332 --> 04:53.335
[Scoffing Laugh]
Sounds like a swell guy.

05:00.092 --> 05:02.595
[Chattering]

05:10.311 --> 05:14.857
Oh, isn't it beautiful? If you
really like it, I'll buy it for you.

05:14.940 --> 05:17.902
Oh, Roy.

05:17.985 --> 05:21.197
What's the matter- afraid
somebody will tell your dad?

05:32.249 --> 05:34.502
He's just jealous.

05:34.585 --> 05:36.587
What do you mean?

05:43.552 --> 05:46.722
My dad's got even more
money than he does.

05:57.691 --> 06:00.194
♪♪ [Continues]

06:02.947 --> 06:04.949
<i>[ Girl Giggles]</i>

06:05.157 --> 06:07.535
<i>♪♪ [ Continues In Distance]</i>

06:13.332 --> 06:15.334
[Engine Stops]

06:17.294 --> 06:20.172
<i>[ Object Clatters ]</i>
Want a slug?

06:20.256 --> 06:23.175
[Sighs] You sure know how
to put a girl in the mood.

06:23.259 --> 06:26.220
Just call me Mr. Romance.

06:26.303 --> 06:29.348
<i>♪♪ [ Continues]</i>

06:29.431 --> 06:31.308
Piece of cake, please.

06:31.433 --> 06:34.353
- Did you see where Pat went?
- Sorry.

06:49.660 --> 06:52.329
[Geese Honking]

07:03.090 --> 07:06.302
That water looks great.

07:06.385 --> 07:08.470
We oughta go for a swim.

07:08.554 --> 07:11.515
- We wouldn't even need suits.
- Roy?

07:11.599 --> 07:14.101
I'm only ribbing you.
I don't want to swim.

07:17.229 --> 07:20.274
You're all I want.
Come on.

07:25.404 --> 07:27.406
Come here, baby.

07:29.825 --> 07:32.036
Roy, I shouldn't.

07:34.663 --> 07:37.207
<i>[ Footsteps In Mud]</i>

07:39.084 --> 07:43.464
[Crowd Applauding] Okay.
And while the boys go powder their noses,

07:43.547 --> 07:47.551
why don't all you chowhounds hustle your
gals over to the refreshment table...

07:47.635 --> 07:49.720
and dig in.
[Laughs]

07:52.222 --> 07:54.975
Roy.

07:55.059 --> 07:57.353
<i>- [ Electricity Crackles]
- Roy?</i>

08:07.946 --> 08:10.658
Come on.

08:10.741 --> 08:13.369
Come on, don't play hard to get.

08:13.452 --> 08:15.496
What about New Year's Eve?

08:15.579 --> 08:18.957
Well, that was different.
I couldn't help myself.

08:21.960 --> 08:25.964
What if somebody sees us? You don't
even have to take your dress off.

08:27.633 --> 08:30.094
[Kissing]
You're so amazing.

08:31.595 --> 08:34.097
If one of your damn soldier friends
shows his face around here,

08:35.349 --> 08:37.351
well, he's gonna wish
he was back overseas.

08:49.488 --> 08:51.573
- [Screaming]
- [ Groaning]

08:51.657 --> 08:55.119
No! No!

08:55.202 --> 08:57.996
No!
[Gasps]

08:58.080 --> 09:01.125
- [ Gasping]
<i>- ♪♪ [Drumroll]</i>

09:01.208 --> 09:04.545
Hey, you alive out there?
[Crowd Shouts, Cheers]

09:04.628 --> 09:06.714
Well, let's hear it!

09:06.797 --> 09:09.299
[Laughing] Yay!
Whoa-oh! [Shouting]

09:36.118 --> 09:38.620
<i>[Hammering ]</i>

09:43.542 --> 09:45.544
Looks a little crooked to me.

09:45.627 --> 09:48.881
Oh, yeah?
How's that?

09:48.964 --> 09:51.341
Maybe a little bit higher.

09:52.551 --> 09:54.970
Like that? Is that better?

09:55.053 --> 09:57.181
Yeah. It looks great.

09:57.264 --> 10:00.058
[Chuckles]
Yeah.

10:00.142 --> 10:02.686
Mark. How about this side?

10:03.854 --> 10:09.276
<i>Well, if it isn't Deputy London
keeping an eye on things.</i>

10:09.359 --> 10:11.487
- Hi, guys.
- Hi.

10:11.570 --> 10:14.323
- Hi, Pam.
- Hi, Mark.

10:14.406 --> 10:16.408
Well, I guess you don't
need me anymore.

10:17.659 --> 10:21.163
- Where you goin'?
- Uh, to drop these off.

10:21.288 --> 10:24.625
- The graduation edition?
- Yeah. We just finished this morning.

10:24.750 --> 10:25.824
You have a spare?

10:25.849 --> 10:28.945
Yeah, but we had to
print these very small,

10:29.004 --> 10:33.300
and I wouldn't want you to strain
your eyes twice in one day.

10:33.383 --> 10:35.719
Well, maybe you can
read it to me over lunch.

10:37.679 --> 10:38.461
Okay.

10:38.486 --> 10:40.832
All right. I gotta stop
by the office first though.

10:40.891 --> 10:43.477
If I don't, the sheriff will kill me.

10:43.560 --> 10:46.522
They haven't had
a graduation dance since 1945...

10:46.605 --> 10:48.607
because Major Chatham
wouldn't allow it.

10:49.733 --> 10:51.735
Well, he'd stop it now if he could.

10:51.819 --> 10:55.489
<i>But he can't. Since the stroke,
no one's even seen him.</i>

10:55.572 --> 10:58.283
You know, I feel sorry for him.

10:58.367 --> 11:01.912
He's all alone in that house, so close to
where he found his daughter and that boy.

11:03.455 --> 11:05.874
State police called
about an hour ago.

11:05.958 --> 11:08.377
Somebody robbed a market
up near Columbus.

11:08.460 --> 11:11.171
<i>Cut some kid up
and took his car.</i>

11:11.255 --> 11:13.924
<i>They think he may
be headed this way.</i>

11:14.007 --> 11:16.760
Are you still gonna leave?

11:16.844 --> 11:20.848
I can't start the summer without fishing.
You know that. I never could.

11:20.931 --> 11:22.933
Besides, you've been here
for two years now.

11:23.016 --> 11:25.561
<i>You can handle anything
that might come along.</i>

11:26.687 --> 11:30.315
Here you go.
You were so anxious to read it before.

11:32.651 --> 11:34.611
“Pam MacDonald.”

11:37.489 --> 11:39.408
I'm impressed.

11:39.491 --> 11:41.910
Thank you.

11:41.994 --> 11:44.788
Check, please.

11:46.123 --> 11:49.501
I guess with the, uh, sheriff leaving,
you'll be on duty tonight, huh?

11:49.585 --> 11:51.587
- Yeah.
- Oh.

11:53.130 --> 11:58.051
I was hoping maybe you could come by
the graduation dance a little later.

11:58.135 --> 12:01.346
Well, maybe I can
come by for a while.

12:03.724 --> 12:05.684
Mark?

12:05.767 --> 12:08.395
Hmm?

12:08.478 --> 12:12.941
You don't think the guy who robbed
that store might come here, do you?

12:13.025 --> 12:15.777
I don't think so.

12:15.861 --> 12:18.614
State police will get him soon.

12:18.697 --> 12:20.657
Yeah, well, until they do,

12:22.868 --> 12:24.995
be careful.

12:25.078 --> 12:26.997
Okay?

12:27.080 --> 12:28.999
Hey, Pam. Over here.

12:30.459 --> 12:32.502
- Hi, Carl.
- Hey. I read your article.

12:32.628 --> 12:34.963
Oh. Wanna go make
out on the point?

12:35.047 --> 12:36.965
[Laughs]
I don't know.

12:37.090 --> 12:39.343
- Is it worth the risk?
- Are you kidding?

12:39.426 --> 12:41.303
Did you taste the punch?

12:41.428 --> 12:43.722
- It's kind of, uh, bland.
- It is now.

12:43.847 --> 12:45.630
But as soon as “El chaperono”
isn't looking, we'll-

12:45.655 --> 12:46.248
Shh!

12:46.350 --> 12:49.353
- Is the punch ready?
- Yes, Miss Allison.

12:49.436 --> 12:51.897
You're gonna
get us all in trouble.

12:52.147 --> 12:55.192
Well, Captain,
if your men are after him,

12:55.275 --> 12:57.527
I don't think there's
anything to worry about.

12:59.029 --> 13:02.449
Yeah, my deputy will let you know
if he sees anything.

13:02.532 --> 13:04.451
Mark.

13:04.534 --> 13:06.453
Oh, yeah. Mm-hmm.
[Chuckles]

13:06.536 --> 13:08.789
He's a good boy.

13:08.872 --> 13:10.832
You're damn right
it's my fishing trip.

13:10.916 --> 13:14.294
And if you bother me
about anything, Bill,

13:14.378 --> 13:18.048
I'll kick your ass
right across the state line, okay?

13:18.131 --> 13:20.050
[Laughing]

13:20.133 --> 13:22.052
Okay. Good-bye.

13:23.679 --> 13:25.973
Now, if you need anything,
you got my number.

13:26.056 --> 13:30.560
The worst you'll probably have will be some
of those kids from the dance running wild.

13:30.644 --> 13:32.813
Now, just remember,

13:32.896 --> 13:35.315
there's still some people
around here who, uh,

13:35.399 --> 13:37.359
won't put up
with that kind of thing.

13:37.442 --> 13:39.152
Yes, sir.

13:39.236 --> 13:41.571
[Laughs]
You'll do fine.

13:41.655 --> 13:44.157
Come on down to Kingsley's
with me.

13:44.241 --> 13:46.618
<i>I've got some things
I gotta pick up.</i>

13:46.702 --> 13:49.663
Oh, no. Major's orders, Ray.

13:51.206 --> 13:53.125
Otto, get out here!

13:53.208 --> 13:55.127
<i>I'm- I'm right at the good part.</i>

13:55.210 --> 13:58.171
Now, goddamn it, the major
doesn't wanna be kept waiting.

13:58.255 --> 14:00.966
All he does is wait...
and watch some girls.

14:01.049 --> 14:04.302
Hey. Have you been
sneaking around again?

14:04.428 --> 14:06.847
Now, I told you-
<i>[Door Opens, Bell Jingles</i>

14:06.930 --> 14:09.099
Now get movin'.
We got customers.

14:10.100 --> 14:12.769
- Well, afternoon, George.
<i>- Hi, Pat.</i>

14:12.853 --> 14:15.480
- Hey, you leavin' today, huh?
- Mm-hmm.

14:19.234 --> 14:21.236
<i>[ Objects Clatter]</i>

14:22.612 --> 14:25.032
<i>[Door Opens, Bell Jingles</i>
Anything else for you today?

14:25.115 --> 14:28.493
Uh, yeah. Just some deodorant.

14:28.577 --> 14:30.495
No sweat.
[Laughing]

14:30.579 --> 14:32.456
<i>Get it?</i>

14:38.795 --> 14:41.298
[ Laughing, Chattering]

14:43.133 --> 14:45.052
<i>[ Bicycle Bell Rings]</i>

14:45.135 --> 14:47.012
- Hi, girls.
- Hey, you.

14:47.137 --> 14:48.148
Finished already?

14:48.173 --> 14:51.207
Yeah, we finally got
that banner stretched out.

14:51.308 --> 14:53.404
What you doin', Deputy,
guarding the store?

14:53.429 --> 14:54.126
Yeah.

14:54.227 --> 14:56.688
- Gonna be at the dance, won't you?
<i>- I'll try.</i>

14:56.772 --> 14:59.483
- Try real hard.
- Hey, how you doin', girls?

15:00.859 --> 15:03.361
Now, what the hell you doin'
still out here?

15:05.489 --> 15:07.407
<i>[ Pat]
I don't know, George.</i>

15:07.491 --> 15:10.077
<i>Sometimes I wonder why
I've taken care of him so long.</i>

15:10.160 --> 15:13.830
Well, I-I gotta go
tend to the customers.

15:13.955 --> 15:18.752
This time, uh, why don't you use those
minnows for bait, huh? [Snaps Fingers]

15:18.835 --> 15:20.837
Bye, Pat.

15:22.047 --> 15:25.801
- Are they graduating this year?
- Yeah.

15:25.884 --> 15:27.886
They're friends
of Pam MacDonald.

15:27.969 --> 15:29.888
They don't seem like her type.

15:29.971 --> 15:33.266
Now, remember,
if you have any problems, call me.

15:33.391 --> 15:35.936
<i>- Have a good time.</i>
- I will.

15:52.536 --> 15:53.954
- Hi.
<i>- Hi.</i>

15:54.079 --> 15:56.289
- What do you think? This one?
- I like it.

15:56.373 --> 15:58.667
Or how about this one?

15:58.750 --> 16:00.794
[Laughing] I don't know
what the difference is.

16:00.877 --> 16:04.548
I mean, with Carl around, it's not
gonna stay on too long anyway, right?

16:04.631 --> 16:08.301
Yeah.
[Chuckles] He is a real animal.

16:08.385 --> 16:11.012
Any of you Pritcher girls
got any rolling papers?

16:11.096 --> 16:13.723
Uh, I think I do.

16:17.936 --> 16:20.230
Thank you very much.
I'll roll you a couple for later.

16:22.023 --> 16:24.818
Carl gave 'em to me.

16:24.901 --> 16:26.820
[Chuckles]

16:26.903 --> 16:30.574
Hey, you're not gonna
mope around tonight, are you?

16:30.657 --> 16:33.618
<i>This is everybody's
last night together.</i>

16:34.661 --> 16:37.539
And some of us will never
see each other again.

16:39.541 --> 16:41.459
Sherry.

16:41.543 --> 16:43.420
I'm worried about Mark.

16:43.545 --> 16:46.339
- He'll come to the dance.
- I know. It's not that.

16:46.423 --> 16:49.676
It's- It's that guy who stabbed
that man in Columbus.

16:49.759 --> 16:52.304
I thought you said
they're about to catch him.

16:52.387 --> 16:54.306
Yeah, that's what Mark says.

16:54.389 --> 16:56.308
[Clicks Tongue]

16:56.391 --> 16:58.393
I wish the sheriff was here.

17:12.281 --> 17:14.201
Hey, Lisa.

17:14.284 --> 17:18.454
I just spilled nail polish
all over your dress.

17:18.579 --> 17:22.917
Yeah, you do and I'll kill you.
<i>[Laughs]</i>

17:23.001 --> 17:25.286
<i>Lisa, you'd better close
those shades.</i>

17:25.310 --> 17:27.445
<i>You're gonna give old man
Chatham another stroke.</i>

17:27.505 --> 17:31.009
Are you kiddin'?
That old guy's harmless.

17:31.092 --> 17:33.428
He can't even get
out of his wheelchair.

17:35.722 --> 17:39.643
<i>Yeah, but there's nothing wrong
with his eyes.</i>

17:39.726 --> 17:42.812
He's been staring at us all semester.

17:42.896 --> 17:45.315
[Laughs]
Oh, yeah?

17:45.398 --> 17:48.777
[Shrieks]

17:48.860 --> 17:50.445
[Laughing]
Lisa!

17:50.528 --> 17:52.656
[Laughing]

17:55.575 --> 17:57.661
Well, he oughta be able
to stand up now.

17:57.744 --> 17:59.663
You're awful.

18:10.048 --> 18:12.550
<i>[ Laughing, Chattering]</i>

18:19.557 --> 18:21.518
[Indistinct]

18:30.068 --> 18:32.070
[Exhales]

18:54.634 --> 18:57.637
<i>[Shower Running]</i>

19:17.073 --> 19:19.034
Sherry. You want me to wait?

19:19.159 --> 19:22.370
- I will if you hurry.
- No. That's okay.

19:22.454 --> 19:24.456
Carl gets real horny
if I make him wait.

19:24.539 --> 19:27.459
[Laughs]
Now who's the animal, huh?

19:27.584 --> 19:29.502
- See you later.
- Bye.

20:05.830 --> 20:07.707
<i>- [Shouts]</i>
- [Screams]

20:07.832 --> 20:11.711
- [Laughs] Do you always walk backwards?
- I thought I heard someone.

20:11.795 --> 20:14.964
I think you need this
a whole lot more than I do.

20:15.090 --> 20:15.892
That's okay.

20:15.917 --> 20:18.325
Maybe it's that dangerous
criminal you were tellin' us about.

20:18.385 --> 20:21.012
Maybe he was trying
to knock over Kingsley's.

20:21.137 --> 20:23.431
[Imitates Gunshot]
[Laughs]

20:23.556 --> 20:26.142
Lisa. Come on, you guys.
Let's go. [Laughing]

20:27.894 --> 20:30.605
[ Laughing, Chattering]

20:49.833 --> 20:52.836
<i>[ Footsteps ]</i>

21:04.389 --> 21:06.391
<i>[ Doorknob Turns]</i>

21:32.000 --> 21:36.004
[Gasps] Jesus, Carl!
You scared the shit outta me.

21:36.129 --> 21:38.047
Door was open.

21:38.131 --> 21:41.384
You know how I get
when I have to wait around.

21:41.468 --> 21:44.220
Maybe I was expecting
somebody else.

21:44.304 --> 21:46.556
Fat chance.

21:46.639 --> 21:48.558
Don't just stand there.
Shut the door.

21:48.641 --> 21:50.560
<i>Aren't you gonna ask me in?</i>

21:50.643 --> 21:52.562
How fast can you
take off your clothes?

21:54.689 --> 21:57.984
Start your stopwatch, coach.
<i>[Shoe Drops]</i>

21:58.067 --> 22:00.028
[Giggles]

22:01.696 --> 22:04.199
<i>[ Shower Continues]</i>

22:23.927 --> 22:27.138
[Muffled Shouting]

22:28.473 --> 22:30.975
[Gasping]

22:36.731 --> 22:39.234
<i>[ Muffled Gasping]</i>

22:47.408 --> 22:50.245
[Groans]

23:17.814 --> 23:22.318
Hurry up, Carl.
I'm turning into a goddamn prune.

23:25.405 --> 23:27.323
[ Kisses, Laughs]

23:27.407 --> 23:28.908
[Gasps]

23:28.992 --> 23:32.370
[Screaming]

23:32.453 --> 23:34.956
[Groaning, Screaming]

23:42.839 --> 23:45.508
[Screaming]

23:49.929 --> 23:52.348
<i>[Screaming Continues, Stops]
♪♪ [ Band: Rock]</i>

23:52.515 --> 23:55.768
<i>[ Man] ♪ I know we'll be together ♪</i>
[Boy] The cake's over here.

23:58.146 --> 24:00.148
I hope it's
big enough for you. There.

24:00.231 --> 24:02.650
- That should do.
- Come on, hot stuff.

24:02.734 --> 24:05.361
Let's go dance.
[Mumbling]

24:08.114 --> 24:11.117
<i>♪♪ [ Continues, Indistinct]</i>

24:16.497 --> 24:19.083
- There you go.
- You got a piece of that for me?

24:19.167 --> 24:22.295
Miss Al.
You havin' a good time?

24:27.258 --> 24:30.219
- Hi.
- Hi.

24:40.021 --> 24:42.732
[Mouthing Words]

25:11.844 --> 25:12.824
Oh. Okay.

25:12.849 --> 25:15.789
<i>♪ If you don't hurt yourself
then you'll hurt someone else ♪</i>

25:15.848 --> 25:17.767
Sure.

25:17.850 --> 25:20.561
<i>♪ Sometimes you learn things
the hard way ♪</i>

25:20.645 --> 25:23.064
<i>♪ Take the path
of least resistance ♪</i>

25:24.565 --> 25:27.026
<i>♪ Make it easy on yourself ♪</i>

25:27.110 --> 25:29.028
How you doin', honey cup?

25:29.112 --> 25:31.823
Hi, Paul.
<i>♪ I know I can do the distance ♪</i>

25:31.906 --> 25:37.870
<i>♪ It doesn't matter
what they say ♪</i>

25:38.996 --> 25:41.499
<i>♪♪ [ Continues]</i>

25:45.169 --> 25:47.130
<i>♪ Oh ♪</i>

25:53.594 --> 25:57.557
<i>♪ You know where you're going
but you don't know what's there ♪</i>

25:57.640 --> 26:01.477
<i>♪ Sometimes you learn things
the hard way ♪</i>

26:01.561 --> 26:03.604
<i>So you take the high road ♪</i>

26:03.688 --> 26:05.690
<i>♪ When the low road is faster ♪</i>
Hi.

26:05.773 --> 26:09.318
<i>♪ Sometimes you do things
the hard way ♪ </i>

26:09.402 --> 26:12.155
- ♪ Try not to hurry ♪
- Well, Mr. Turner, what do you think?

26:12.238 --> 26:14.657
Oh, it's exciting.
Just like the good old days.

26:14.741 --> 26:16.659
Except I had more hair then.
[Laughs]

26:16.743 --> 26:20.037
♪ Just take the path
of least resistance ♪

26:21.247 --> 26:24.000
♪ Make it easy on yourself ♪

26:24.083 --> 26:26.419
Guess you've been around here
longer than anyone.

26:26.502 --> 26:28.421
Yeah. Forty years.

26:28.504 --> 26:32.467
Good having the girls back.
Makes me feel young again.

26:36.512 --> 26:38.514
Thanks for the dance.

26:38.598 --> 26:41.350
Aw, come on.
I'm sorry.

26:41.434 --> 26:43.352
It's all right.

26:43.436 --> 26:45.563
- Deputy, that was fun.
<i>- [Punch Splashes]</i>

26:45.646 --> 26:47.648
Oh.
[Laughs]

26:49.817 --> 26:52.361
- Uh- Where you goin'?
- I'm going back to the dorm to change.

26:52.445 --> 26:54.447
I'm sorry.

26:54.530 --> 26:57.033
Don't be. Okay?
Don't be sorry.

26:59.410 --> 27:02.705
[Laughs]
<i>♪ But when they find out what you've got ♪</i>

27:02.789 --> 27:05.458
<i>♪♪ [ Continues, Muffled]</i>

27:12.465 --> 27:14.467
<i>[ Girl]
Hi, Lizzy.</i>

28:09.605 --> 28:13.067
<i>[Shower Running]</i>

28:13.150 --> 28:15.486
[Sighs]

28:17.905 --> 28:21.200
Sherry? It's only me,
and I'm closing the door.

28:28.791 --> 28:31.294
[Creaking]

29:33.064 --> 29:35.024
Shit.
[Snaps Fingers]

30:00.716 --> 30:04.220
<i>[ Door Closes ]
[ Floor Creaks]</i>

30:20.820 --> 30:22.738
<i>[ Footsteps On Stairs]</i>

30:37.086 --> 30:39.714
Anne! Anne!

30:42.049 --> 30:43.968
Betty! Betty!

31:03.779 --> 31:06.282
<i>Help! Help!</i>

31:43.736 --> 31:46.614
[ Gasping ]
No!

31:46.697 --> 31:48.157
Let go!

31:50.701 --> 31:54.121
[Whimpers]
Please!

31:55.164 --> 31:58.375
Stop it! No! No!

31:58.459 --> 32:00.002
Please let go!

32:11.722 --> 32:13.933
- [Gasps] Mark!
- What's wrong?

32:14.016 --> 32:16.060
- Oh, God.
- What happened? What happened?

32:16.185 --> 32:19.396
- It's all right. What's the matter?
- Mark. Somebody was chasing me.

32:19.480 --> 32:21.899
Somebody was chasing me,
and Major Chatham grabbed me.

32:22.024 --> 32:23.943
- Major Chatham?
- Uh-huh.

32:24.026 --> 32:25.903
Mark, he hurt my arm.

32:26.028 --> 32:27.645
What the hell was Major Chatham
doing down here?

32:27.670 --> 32:28.263
I don't know.

32:28.364 --> 32:31.158
- And he- And he chased you?
- No. I don't know who chased me.

32:31.242 --> 32:33.661
All I saw was, um, boots
and some kind of uniform.

32:33.744 --> 32:37.123
Are you okay? All right,
I'm gonna take a look around.

32:37.206 --> 32:39.542
My jeep's right there. Stay there.
I'll be right back.

32:39.625 --> 32:41.627
Be right back.

34:43.123 --> 34:45.125
[Exhales]

34:52.257 --> 34:54.176
[Gasps, Exhales]

34:54.260 --> 34:56.178
Did you find anything?

34:56.262 --> 34:58.889
I found wheelchair marks
and boot tracks too.

34:59.014 --> 35:01.141
- Did you look in the dorm?
- No.

35:02.559 --> 35:04.895
- Here.
- Mark, Sherry's in there.

35:05.020 --> 35:07.690
- Carl's with her.
- Okay.

36:21.013 --> 36:24.266
Let's go.
Where?

36:24.350 --> 36:26.352
Major Chatham's.

37:06.016 --> 37:07.935
[Pounding]

37:08.018 --> 37:10.020
Major Chatham?

37:18.362 --> 37:20.364
Major Chatham!

37:21.782 --> 37:23.784
Let's try around back.

37:27.329 --> 37:29.331
[Pam]
Major Chatham!

37:37.631 --> 37:40.634
<i>[ Clock Ticking ]</i>

38:32.769 --> 38:34.897
Major Chatham?

38:50.579 --> 38:52.581
Major Chatham!

39:02.799 --> 39:05.802
<i>[ Floor Creaking]</i>

39:36.333 --> 39:38.669
<i>[ Mark]
Major Chatham!</i>

39:47.386 --> 39:49.388
<i>Mark.</i>

40:44.109 --> 40:46.111
This is Francis Chatham.

40:50.699 --> 40:52.701
I'm gonna take a look upstairs.

41:19.311 --> 41:22.314
<i>[ Stairs Creaking]</i>

41:31.907 --> 41:33.825
Major Chatham?

42:09.695 --> 42:11.697
<i>[ Floor Creaks]</i>

44:06.520 --> 44:08.980
[Gasps]
Oh, Mark, you scared me.

44:09.064 --> 44:11.004
Everything's covered upstairs.

44:11.029 --> 44:13.008
Chatham probably hasn't even been
up there since his last stroke.

44:13.109 --> 44:15.445
- You find anything?
- Look at this.

44:15.570 --> 44:19.241
- So what?
- It's the major's daughter.

44:19.324 --> 44:22.744
Francis Rosemary Chatham.
They must have called her Rose.

44:22.828 --> 44:25.497
And look. See? I found
a pressed rose in the yearbook.

44:25.580 --> 44:28.333
And the killer left behind
a rose in her hands.

44:31.044 --> 44:35.048
Didn't you read my article?
They never found out who did it.

44:35.131 --> 44:38.510
But it had to be someone in town,
someone who knew that she was called Rose,

44:38.593 --> 44:40.679
and, Mark, that guy
still might be around here.

44:40.762 --> 44:42.337
Oh, man. I don't believe this.

44:42.362 --> 44:44.039
You're talking about something that
happened over 30 years ago.

44:45.058 --> 44:49.354
Pam. The guy who chased you may be the one
the state police are looking for right now.

44:50.730 --> 44:52.754
I say let's get the hell
out of here

44:52.779 --> 44:54.758
and go to the dance and see
that everyone stays inside.

44:54.818 --> 44:56.778
Maybe you should call the sheriff.

44:57.946 --> 45:00.824
- Thanks.
- I'm sorry.

45:01.825 --> 45:04.536
Okay. I didn't mean that.

45:08.164 --> 45:10.125
It's all right.

45:12.586 --> 45:14.504
Let's go.

45:23.221 --> 45:24.556
<i>♪♪ [ Rock, Muffled]</i>
[ Retches]

45:24.639 --> 45:27.684
- Paul, are you okay?
- Oh- [Coughs] God.

45:28.768 --> 45:31.354
I think I'm gonna throw up again.
[Retches]

45:35.984 --> 45:40.572
<i>♪ Can't take this no more
But I wanna see blood on the floor ♪</i>

45:40.655 --> 45:45.076
♪ Standing in the spotlight
I hope I can see her bleed ♪

45:45.160 --> 45:48.038
♪ I want to see her bleed ♪

45:48.121 --> 45:51.291
♪ Don't turn off the spotlight
I still want to see her bleed ♪

45:51.416 --> 45:54.669
- Is Paul still in here?
- Yeah. He's sick as a dog.

45:54.753 --> 45:57.088
[ Coughs, Retches]

45:59.507 --> 46:01.426
I'm gonna go cool off, Paul.

46:01.509 --> 46:05.555
When you get tired of hugging the toilet,
you can find me up at Garner's pool.

46:10.685 --> 46:14.105
<i>♪ I'm lonely
and I wanna go home alone ♪</i>

46:14.189 --> 46:16.107
There she is.

46:18.443 --> 46:21.279
<i>♪ I'm lonely
Don't leave me alone ♪</i>

46:21.363 --> 46:25.116
You mean there was someone actually in
the dorm? Are you sure you're all right?

46:25.200 --> 46:27.535
- I'm fine.
- God. It must have been terrible.

46:27.619 --> 46:29.621
I want you to tell everyone
to stay put.

46:29.704 --> 46:32.582
Right. I-I'll make
an announcement right away.

46:32.666 --> 46:35.669
<i>♪♪ [ Continues]</i>

46:39.631 --> 46:42.300
[indistinct]
♪ : [ Stops ]

46:43.385 --> 46:45.303
Very important announcement to make.

46:45.387 --> 46:48.390
Uh, is this thing on still?
Do you think-

46:48.473 --> 46:50.475
Hello?
Testing- [Blows] [Feedback]

46:50.558 --> 46:56.064
Hello? Uh, attention. Could I have your
attention, please, ladies and gentlemen?

46:56.147 --> 46:59.317
Uh, Deputy London
has just informed me...

46:59.401 --> 47:04.155
that a prowler has been seen
around the campus, and, uh-

47:04.239 --> 47:06.157
Well, he could be dangerous.

47:06.241 --> 47:10.245
<i>Now, I know this won't be very popular,
but I'm gonna have to ask...</i>

47:10.328 --> 47:14.290
that everybody please stay in the building
until we know more about this.

47:14.416 --> 47:18.336
<i>[ Groaning]</i>
Which shouldn't be too long, okay?

47:18.420 --> 47:22.882
So everybody just relax
and enjoy the dance and the music.

47:22.966 --> 47:25.051
- [Feedback]
- Shit.

47:25.135 --> 47:27.345
[All Laughing]

47:28.763 --> 47:31.433
Oh. Thank you.

47:31.516 --> 47:33.518
<i>Oh.
[ Toilet Flushes ]</i>

47:33.601 --> 47:36.604
I'll probably puke
in the damn pool.

47:36.688 --> 47:38.732
Psst!

47:40.025 --> 47:42.861
Hi. I'm back.
Who turned off the band?

47:42.986 --> 47:45.450
Miss Allison just made
an announcement.

47:45.475 --> 47:47.681
There's some kind of prowler
outside or something.

47:47.741 --> 47:49.743
Maybe we should tell her Lisa left.

47:49.826 --> 47:52.245
Nah. Paul will be with her.
She'll be okay.

47:52.328 --> 47:54.247
<i>[ Drumsticks Tapping ]
[ Man ] One, two, three!</i>

47:54.330 --> 47:57.292
♪♪ <i>[Rock]</i>
Hey, baby.

47:57.375 --> 48:00.128
Let's struggle. Come on.

48:01.171 --> 48:02.918
Wait a minute, Paul.
You're gonna have to wait

48:02.943 --> 48:04.615
- a while before you go outside.
- For what?

48:04.716 --> 48:06.776
Paul, hold on. Just listen
to me for a minute, okay?

48:06.801 --> 48:08.160
What the fuck's goin' on here?

48:44.839 --> 48:49.010
♪ Don't go ♪

48:49.135 --> 48:50.980
I don't give a shit
about any goddamn prowler.

48:51.005 --> 48:52.496
All right.
Now just settle down!

48:52.555 --> 48:54.808
- Calm down, buddy.
- Leave me alone! Okay, okay.

48:54.891 --> 48:58.812
I want this boy arrested! We don't have
to stand for this kind of thing here.

48:58.895 --> 49:02.398
I want him out of here!
Or am I gonna have to call the sheriff?

49:02.482 --> 49:04.984
Oh, God.
This is stupid, man.

49:06.152 --> 49:08.321
All right, look.
I'm gettin' him out of here. Okay?

49:08.404 --> 49:11.574
Look. Can you handle everything here?
Come on! Come on.

49:20.708 --> 49:23.628
[Panting]

49:43.481 --> 49:45.733
[Grunts]

49:59.205 --> 50:02.625
[Gasping]

50:27.317 --> 50:30.403
[Screaming]

51:16.032 --> 51:17.951
<i>♪♪ [ Continues ]</i>
She's where?

51:18.034 --> 51:20.870
Okay, I think that she went out
to the pool, just to cool off.

51:20.954 --> 51:22.872
See, it was
before the announcement.

51:22.956 --> 51:24.874
No, somebody's
gonna have to go get her.

51:27.627 --> 51:30.255
If you see Mr. Turner,
just tell him where I've gone.

51:33.716 --> 51:35.760
Think I just got Lisa in trouble.

51:37.178 --> 51:39.764
[Laughing]
[Muttering]

51:40.765 --> 51:42.934
Paul.

51:43.017 --> 51:44.978
Gonna slap the cuffs on me, chief?

51:49.190 --> 51:51.526
Book 'em, Pam-o.
[Chuckles]

51:55.154 --> 51:57.156
Lisa?

52:06.582 --> 52:08.543
Lisa?

52:10.962 --> 52:12.922
Lisa?

52:19.804 --> 52:24.350
<i>♪♪ [ Continues, Loud]</i> I am not going outside
until they catch the prowler. That's it.

52:24.434 --> 52:26.686
We don't have to go-

52:26.769 --> 52:29.314
We don't have to go outside.

52:29.397 --> 52:32.608
There's a perfect place
down in the basement. I know it.

52:32.692 --> 52:35.695
I mean, people here, they use it
all the time for parties and stuff.

52:35.778 --> 52:38.573
Ha! Right!
What kind of people?

52:38.656 --> 52:42.076
Come on, Sally. It's great. I'll show you.
Come on. Come on.

52:54.756 --> 52:56.674
- Am I okay?
- Yeah.

52:56.758 --> 52:58.760
Yeah?

53:06.100 --> 53:08.478
I thought you knew
where this place was.

53:08.561 --> 53:11.814
Ah, that's the beauty of it.
It's difficult to find.

53:11.898 --> 53:14.359
That way, there's no chance
of being interrupted.

53:20.281 --> 53:22.283
[Sally]
Hang on.

53:27.038 --> 53:29.165
[Lights Clatter]
Hey.

53:43.763 --> 53:45.681
It's around here somewhere.
<i>[ Clattering ]</i>

53:59.529 --> 54:03.199
[Gasping]

54:12.125 --> 54:15.670
[Gasping, Choking]

54:15.753 --> 54:17.922
[Muffled Scream]

54:18.005 --> 54:19.340
[Groaning]

54:19.424 --> 54:23.344
[Choking]

54:31.144 --> 54:33.062
Shit.

54:36.607 --> 54:39.569
Hey! Warden!
We're bustin' out of here at midnight!

54:39.652 --> 54:43.156
<i>You can't keep me in here!</i>

54:43.281 --> 54:46.075
- What are you charging him with?
- Disturbing the peace.

54:46.159 --> 54:50.746
Hey, you can't keep me in here. My boys will
spring me as soon as they hear about this.

54:50.830 --> 54:54.041
Hey! Keep it down in there!

54:54.125 --> 54:58.045
Ooh! Look out, boys!
The marshal's comin' with his rubber hose!

54:59.422 --> 55:01.757
Paul, shut up!

55:18.232 --> 55:20.735
<i>[ Soft Footsteps]</i>

55:33.331 --> 55:35.249
<i>[ Floorboard Creeks]</i>

55:41.756 --> 55:43.674
I heard something.
[Sniffles]

55:45.176 --> 55:47.094
It was probably just the wind.

55:57.063 --> 56:01.192
In the basement?
Hmm?

56:01.275 --> 56:05.404
[Chuckling]
Basement!

56:08.616 --> 56:11.577
Why don't we
check out the dorm again?

56:11.702 --> 56:13.604
You don't think he'd still be
there, do you?

56:13.629 --> 56:14.938
It's all we have to go on.

56:14.997 --> 56:17.041
Oh, but Mark,
what about Major Chatham?

56:17.124 --> 56:19.794
I'm not gonna break into the
man's house twice in one night.

56:21.462 --> 56:24.382
Well. Lookee here.

56:24.465 --> 56:27.885
Now, George left you in charge here.

56:27.969 --> 56:30.304
Can't you keep them kids under control?

56:30.388 --> 56:32.515
What are you doing here, Kingsley?

56:34.684 --> 56:37.562
It's that damn graduation thing.

56:37.645 --> 56:40.815
We haven't had any trouble out of that
college for more than 30 years, and...

56:42.525 --> 56:46.153
now they have to
start that damn thing over again.

56:46.237 --> 56:47.707
What do you mean?

56:47.732 --> 56:52.142
There's a bunch of kids
over there in the cemetery.

56:52.201 --> 56:54.870
I know what they're doin' in there.

56:54.954 --> 56:57.540
Now, what are they
doing in there, Kingsley?

56:57.623 --> 57:01.836
Hell, it was dark.
I couldn't <i>see</i> anything.

57:01.919 --> 57:05.006
Well, if you couldn't see anything,
why don't you just go home?

57:08.509 --> 57:10.469
Sure.

57:11.637 --> 57:14.557
But that gate was wide open.

57:18.352 --> 57:20.313
[Footsteps Sloshing]

57:21.731 --> 57:23.858
The gate's supposed
to be locked at night.

57:25.192 --> 57:27.445
I wonder what he was doing
wandering around down there.

57:28.696 --> 57:31.532
<i>[ Crickets Chirping]</i>

57:47.214 --> 57:50.635
[Engine Stops] [Exhales]
Watch the road.

57:50.718 --> 57:53.304
I'm gonna see what I can find
out there, okay?

57:53.387 --> 57:55.348
Okay.

01:01:14.004 --> 01:01:16.841
<i>[ Footsteps ]</i>

01:01:33.023 --> 01:01:35.609
[Screaming]
Mark!

01:01:45.244 --> 01:01:48.163
Mark! Mark! Mark.

01:01:48.247 --> 01:01:50.875
I saw somebody.
I think it was Otto Hahn!

01:01:50.958 --> 01:01:53.002
I- H-He was looking at me
through the window.

01:01:53.085 --> 01:01:55.004
<i>I found an open grave out there.</i>

01:02:03.888 --> 01:02:05.806
It's been opened.

01:02:27.119 --> 01:02:29.038
[Grunts]

01:02:51.060 --> 01:02:54.605
<i>[ Whimpering]
Oh, Lisa.</i>

01:02:54.688 --> 01:02:57.274
[ Sobbing ]
No!

01:02:58.901 --> 01:03:00.861
No!

01:03:12.331 --> 01:03:15.209
<i>[ Pam Sobs]</i>

01:03:24.468 --> 01:03:26.387
[Crying]

01:03:26.595 --> 01:03:30.057
<i>[ Phone Ringing]</i>

01:03:39.233 --> 01:03:42.945
[Ringing Continues]

01:03:48.033 --> 01:03:49.086
Ocoee Lodge.

01:03:49.111 --> 01:03:52.270
Hello, yeah. Uh, could I please
speak to Sheriff George Fraser?

01:03:52.329 --> 01:03:55.457
He should have checked in today.

01:03:55.541 --> 01:03:59.086
Well, I just come on an hour ago.

01:04:00.254 --> 01:04:02.256
Let me check and see
what cabin he's in.

01:04:05.426 --> 01:04:07.428
♪ ♪ [ Humming]

01:04:09.221 --> 01:04:11.417
Look, buddy. This is an emergency.

01:04:11.442 --> 01:04:13.458
I need to get in touch with him right away.
He's in, uh...

01:04:14.685 --> 01:04:16.770
Lake Cabin Number 7.

01:04:18.355 --> 01:04:20.357
Most everybody's asleep now.

01:04:21.859 --> 01:04:23.777
Uh-huh.

01:04:24.945 --> 01:04:27.448
Well, why don't I
just run out and get him?

01:04:36.457 --> 01:04:39.293
[Clatters]
<i>[Dog Barking In Distance]</i>

01:04:54.308 --> 01:04:56.310
[Exhales]

01:05:29.009 --> 01:05:30.761
[Spits]

01:05:39.561 --> 01:05:41.563
[Clatters]

01:05:50.697 --> 01:05:53.992
- He ain't in his cabin.
- Well, do you know where he went?

01:05:55.410 --> 01:05:58.705
I told you. I just come on an hour ago.
I ain't seen him.

01:06:00.749 --> 01:06:04.461
I know a bunch of' em were goin'
night fishing for crappie up in, uh-

01:06:05.587 --> 01:06:09.383
Oh, shoot. Where were they going? Uh-

01:06:09.466 --> 01:06:12.261
Look, could you take a message?

01:06:12.344 --> 01:06:15.889
Yeah. I could take a message.

01:06:16.890 --> 01:06:19.059
Wait till I get a pencil.

01:06:27.526 --> 01:06:29.444
[ Scoffs ]

01:06:33.907 --> 01:06:37.828
[Sighs]
All right. Shoot.

01:06:37.911 --> 01:06:42.541
Yeah. Tell him to call Mark London. Tell
him to get in touch with me right away.

01:06:44.084 --> 01:06:47.421
All right. I'll tell him.

01:06:49.298 --> 01:06:51.258
Bye.

01:06:52.551 --> 01:06:54.928
<i>[ Handset Settles In Cradle]</i>

01:06:57.973 --> 01:07:02.477
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>
Mark? Mark, who are you calling?

01:07:02.561 --> 01:07:04.688
State police.

01:07:04.771 --> 01:07:06.732
[Dialing]

01:07:15.949 --> 01:07:18.401
Yeah. This is Deputy Mark
London from Avalon Bay.

01:07:18.426 --> 01:07:20.436
Could I please speak
to Captain Jenkins?

01:07:22.206 --> 01:07:24.958
Yeah, I'll hold.

01:07:25.042 --> 01:07:26.960
[Snoring]

01:07:51.944 --> 01:07:56.406
<i>[ Cartridges Clattering]</i>

01:08:01.620 --> 01:08:03.914
When will they be here?

01:08:03.997 --> 01:08:06.083
Less than half an hour.

01:08:06.166 --> 01:08:08.543
They caught the man
who robbed the store three hours ago.

01:08:08.627 --> 01:08:10.629
He couldn't have killed Lisa.

01:08:10.754 --> 01:08:14.925
That was Rose Chatham's grave we
found, wasn't it? I don't know.

01:08:15.008 --> 01:08:19.179
Mark, the same man who
killed her killed Lisa.

01:08:21.682 --> 01:08:26.103
<i>♪♪ [ Band: Rock]</i>

01:08:26.228 --> 01:08:29.731
[Engine Stops]
Why are we stopping here?

01:08:29.814 --> 01:08:32.901
I want you to go inside
and see if everything's under control.

01:08:32.984 --> 01:08:35.362
- All right?
- All right. I'll be right back.

01:08:37.197 --> 01:08:39.283
Pam?

01:08:39.366 --> 01:08:42.327
I want you to stay at the dance.

01:08:42.452 --> 01:08:45.622
- What?
<i>- I'm going up to Chatham's alone.</i>

01:08:45.706 --> 01:08:48.125
Mark, that doesn't make any sense.

01:08:48.207 --> 01:08:51.420
I don't wanna drag you around
anymore, okay?

01:08:51.545 --> 01:08:54.548
Drag me around? What are you talking about?
<i>[Engine Starts ]</i>

01:08:54.673 --> 01:08:55.674
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

01:08:55.698 --> 01:08:58.701
All right. That's fine, Mark!
You just go play sheriff, all right?

01:08:59.761 --> 01:09:01.721
[Exhales]

01:09:27.080 --> 01:09:29.041
Let's go.

01:09:46.767 --> 01:09:48.685
[Engine Stops]

01:10:30.227 --> 01:10:32.145
I'm going upstairs.

01:13:09.344 --> 01:13:11.304
Mark?

01:13:14.015 --> 01:13:15.892
Mark!

01:13:16.017 --> 01:13:19.604
- What happened?
- <i>I don't know!</i>

01:13:22.315 --> 01:13:25.443
<i>[ Switch Clicking]</i>

01:13:31.783 --> 01:13:34.619
<i>[ Floorboards Creaking]</i>

01:13:34.703 --> 01:13:37.330
Must be the fuse.
I'll go down and check it.

01:15:16.304 --> 01:15:20.350
<i>[ Screams ]
No! No!</i>

01:15:21.851 --> 01:15:24.646
[Gasps]

01:15:25.814 --> 01:15:28.608
I'm here for our date, Rose.

01:15:32.278 --> 01:15:35.949
[Gasping]
No! No! No!

01:15:36.032 --> 01:15:38.243
No! No!

01:15:38.326 --> 01:15:43.039
No! Mark! Mark! Mark!

01:15:43.123 --> 01:15:45.417
No! No!

01:17:41.115 --> 01:17:43.743
<i>[ Objects Smashing ]</i>

01:18:12.605 --> 01:18:14.566
<i>[ Glass Shattering ]</i>

01:18:55.148 --> 01:18:57.901
<i>[ Glass Shattering ]</i>

01:19:05.909 --> 01:19:07.952
<i>[ Objects Clattering]</i>

01:19:32.769 --> 01:19:35.355
Oh!

01:19:37.523 --> 01:19:42.195
No! No!

01:20:02.840 --> 01:20:03.925
[Screams]

01:20:21.526 --> 01:20:23.444
<i>Oh.</i>

01:20:47.176 --> 01:20:49.429
[Screams]

01:20:54.559 --> 01:20:57.020
[Screams]

01:20:57.103 --> 01:21:00.106
No!
[Grunts]

01:21:10.950 --> 01:21:15.580
[Gasping]
[Grunting]

01:21:20.084 --> 01:21:22.754
[Gasping, Coughing]

01:21:31.512 --> 01:21:34.891
<i>Sheriff. Sheriff!</i>

01:21:34.974 --> 01:21:37.477
[ Softly]
Why? Why?

01:21:38.519 --> 01:21:41.981
[Grunts]
Why?

01:21:42.065 --> 01:21:43.816
<i>Why?</i>

01:22:12.595 --> 01:22:14.764
[Exhales]

01:22:15.973 --> 01:22:18.184
Go on upstairs.
I better talk to this guy.

01:22:25.942 --> 01:22:27.860
[ Kisses]

01:22:54.262 --> 01:22:57.765
[No Audible Dialogue]

01:23:02.103 --> 01:23:05.273
<i>[Shower Running]</i>

01:23:58.075 --> 01:24:00.786
[No Audible Dialogue]

01:24:26.604 --> 01:24:30.274
[Screaming]

01:24:38.783 --> 01:24:41.577
<i>[ Screaming Continues]</i>

01:24:41.661 --> 01:24:43.663
No!
